<quantity id="4CD19B7EFFAAE27734F5ABA2FDE7FF26" box="[471,606,222,249]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.05" metricValueMax="8.6" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" unit="mm" value="8.05" valueMax="8.6" valueMin="7.5">7.5–8.6 mm</quantity>
(
<typeStatus id="54928839FFAAE277374EABA3FD69FF26" box="[620,720,223,249]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity id="4CD19B7EFFAAE27737F4ABA3FC89FF26" box="[726,816,223,249]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.6" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" unit="mm" value="8.6">8.6 mm</quantity>
); width: 
<quantity id="4CD19B7EFFAAE27736B1ABA3FBA3FF26" box="[915,1050,223,249]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="2.7">2.7–3.3 mm</quantity>
(
<typeStatus id="54928839FFAAE277310AABA3FB35FF26" box="[1064,1164,223,249]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity id="4CD19B7EFFAAE27731B1ABA3FB54FF26" box="[1171,1261,223,249]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96369BFFAAE27735E5AA7FFE28FEC2" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,609]" box="[199,401,259,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">Female unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96369BFFAAE27735E5AA5BFAD9FE9E" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,609]" box="[199,1376,295,321]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">
Etymology. The specific epithet is derived from the Latin expression for the sky blue colour “ 
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE27731C2AA5BFAF4FE9E" box="[1248,1357,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">caeruleus</emphasis>
”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96369BFFAAE27735E5AA37FD55FEBA" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,609]" box="[199,748,331,357]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">
Distribution. 
<collectingCountry id="F33E760BFFAAE277347FAA37FD51FEBA" box="[349,744,331,357]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">Democratic Republic of the Congo</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96369BFFAAE27735E5AA13FBB5FE2A" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">
Differential diagnosis. Besides the blue colouration 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFAAE2773632AA13FBADFE56" authority="Bílý, 2020" authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2020" box="[784,1044,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caerulea" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE2773632AA13FCCCFE56" box="[784,885,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">Anthaxia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE27736A4AA13FC18FE57" box="[902,929,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE2773690AA13FBADFE56" box="[946,1044,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">caerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE2773139AA13FBCCFE56" bold="true" box="[1051,1141,367,393]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26E57F2FFAAE2773139AA13FBCCFE56" box="[1051,1141,367,393]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFAAE27735FDAAEFFEC5FE72" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1898" box="[223,380,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE27735FDAAEFFF41FE72" box="[223,248,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE277342AAAEFFE9DFE73" box="[264,292,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE2773416AAEFFEC5FE72" box="[308,380,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group by the sculpture of the pronotal disc which consists of the fine, transverse cells without central grains, truncate to weakly emarginate anal ventrite, relatively long elytra (twice as long as wide) and also by the different shape of aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="13122A1EFFAAE277377BAAA7FD12FE2A" box="[601,683,475,501]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="8.[151,212,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,1174,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-414@8.[151,1436,1173,1773]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGS. 16–22. Aedeagi (not in scale). 16—Anthaxia (Haplathaxia) aethiopica sp. nov., holotype; 17—A. (H.) caerulea sp. nov., holotype; 18—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans, 1898 (RSA, Limpopo); 19—A. (H.) keniae Théry, 1941 (Kenya, Kiserian); 20—A. (H.) komareki Obenberger, 1931, holotype; 21—A. (H.) occidentalis sp. nov., holotype; 22—A. (H.) pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408013/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) and male metatibiae (
<figureCitation id="13122A1EFFAAE2773689AAA7FC46FE2A" box="[939,1023,475,501]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[151,212,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,1318,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-459@9.[151,1435,1317,1894]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS. 23–28. Male metatibiae (not in scale). 23—Anthaxia (Haplathaxia) aethiopica sp. nov., holotype; 24—A. (H.) caerulea sp. nov., holotype; 25—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans, 1898 (RSA, Limpopo); 26—A. (H.) keniae Théry, 1941 (Kenya, Kiserian); 27—A. (H.) occidentalis sp. nov., holotype; 28—A. (H.) pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408017/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96369BFFAAE27735E5AA83FB3EFDBE" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFAAE27735E5AA83FE72FDC6" authority="Bílý, 2020" authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2020" box="[199,459,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caerulea" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE27735E5AA83FE95FDC6" box="[199,300,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">Anthaxia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE277341FAA83FEE0FDC7" box="[317,345,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE277344BAA83FE72FDC6" box="[361,459,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">caerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE27734F0AA83FD94FDC6" bold="true" box="[466,557,511,537]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26E57F2FFAAE27734F0AA83FD94FDC6" box="[466,557,511,537]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
seems to be distributed in the humid, tropical part of 
<collectingCountry id="F33E760BFFAAE27731A8AA83FB7DFDC6" box="[1162,1220,511,537]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">DRC</collectingCountry>
unlike the sympatric 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFAAE277359EA95FFEE3FDE2" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1898" box="[188,346,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE277359EA95FFF6CFDE2" box="[188,213,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE27735C7A95FFEB8FDE3" box="[229,257,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE2773430A95FFEE3FDE2" box="[274,346,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which follows the less humid, savanna biotopes of the eastern and southern parts of 
<collectingCountry id="F33E760BFFAAE2773035A95FFAEDFDE2" box="[1303,1364,547,573]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">DRC</collectingCountry>
. More specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFAAE2773413A93BFE5EFDBE" authority="Bílý, 2020" authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2020" box="[305,487,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caerulea" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE2773413A93BFEF3FDBE" box="[305,330,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE2773478A93BFECCFDBF" box="[346,373,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE27734A7A93BFE5EFDBE" box="[389,487,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">caerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFAAE27734CCA93BFDF1FDBE" bold="true" box="[494,584,583,609]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26E57F2FFAAE27734CCA93BFDF1FDBE" box="[494,584,583,609]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are needed, of course, for any further speculations.
</paragraph>
